<subSubSection id="FEDA6547FF93C845FF7ED379FDF97304" pageId="14" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B67F36CCFF93C845FF7ED379FDF97304" blockId="14.[144,1248,634,1072]" pageId="14">
<materialsCitation id="06A83C91FF93C845FF7ED379FDE67304" location="Marajo Island" municipality="Rio Madeira" pageId="14" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Amazonas and Para">
DISTRIBUTION: Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="71C04D4FFF93C845FD8DD378FCF872BA" authorityName=": Ellerman" authorityYear="1940" box="[563,819,634,660]" class="Mammalia" family="Erethizontidae" genus="Coendou" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nycthemera">
<emphasis id="84B4EADEFF93C845FD8DD378FCF872BA" box="[563,819,634,660]" italics="true" pageId="14">Coendou nycthemera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been collected from the 
<collectingMunicipality id="561BACB6FF93C845FB08D378FF397294" pageId="14">Rio Madeira</collectingMunicipality>
eastward along the right (south) bank of the Amazon to 
<location id="B31F6017FF93C845FC3BD3A2FBEC7294" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:3E6987DAFF93C845FE56D1FBFCAB7401:B31F6017FF93C845FC3BD3A2FBEC7294" box="[901,1063,672,698]" municipality="Rio Madeira" name="Marajo Island" pageId="14" stateProvince="Amazonas and Para">Marajó Island</location>
in the Brazilian states of 
<collectingRegion id="7404F82EFF93C845FF45D3C7FE2172F1" box="[251,490,709,735]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="14">Amazonas and Pará</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D2514B3DFF93C845FE42D3C7FCE872F1" author="Handley, C. O., Jr. &amp; R. H. Pine" box="[508,803,709,735]" pageId="14" pagination="237 - 244" refId="ref21137" refString="Handley, C. O., Jr., and R. H. Pine. 1992. A new species of prehensile-tailed porcupine, genus Coendou Lacepede, from Brazil. Mammalia 56: 237 - 244." type="journal article" year="1992">Handley and Pine, 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Interviews with indigenous hunters suggest that the range of this species also extends into the adjacent Atlantic coastal watershed of 
<collectingRegion id="7404F82EFF93C845FF11D212FEE37304" box="[175,296,784,810]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="14">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
(Oliveira et al., 2007)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FEDA6547FF93C845FF7ED237FCAB7401" pageId="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B67F36CCFF93C845FF7ED237FF217424" blockId="14.[144,1248,634,1072]" pageId="14">
REMARKS: The authorship of this species has often been misattributed; see Voss and Angermann (1997) for nomenclatural details. Olfers’ (1818) original Latin description of 
<taxonomicName id="71C04D4FFF93C845FBC9D258FED273B4" authorityName=": Ellerman" authorityYear="1940" class="Mammalia" family="Erethizontidae" genus="Coendou" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nycthemera">
<emphasis id="84B4EADEFF93C845FBC9D258FED273B4" italics="true" pageId="14">Coendou nycthemera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is virtually useless, but detailed morphological descriptions were provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="D2514B3DFF93C845FF2ED2A7FE0A7391" author="Handley, C. O., Jr. &amp; R. H. Pine" box="[144,449,933,959]" pageId="14" pagination="237 - 244" refId="ref21137" refString="Handley, C. O., Jr., and R. H. Pine. 1992. A new species of prehensile-tailed porcupine, genus Coendou Lacepede, from Brazil. Mammalia 56: 237 - 244." type="journal article" year="1992">Handley and Pine (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, Emmons and Feer (1997), and Voss and Angermann (1997). This species has historically been confused with 
<emphasis id="84B4EADEFF93C845FD36D2C9FD3173CA" box="[648,762,970,997]" italics="true" pageId="14">
<taxonomicName id="71C04D4FFF93C845FD36D2C9FD3D73CA" authorityName=": Tate" authorityYear="1935" box="[648,758,970,997]" class="Mammalia" family="Erethizontidae" genus="Coendou" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bicolor">C. bicolor</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
a substantially larger western Amazonian species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B67F36CCFF93C845FF7ED517FCAB7401" blockId="14.[144,1248,634,1072]" box="[192,864,1045,1072]" pageId="14">SPECIMENS EXAMINED: See Voss and Angermann (1997).</paragraph>
